
[TestRuleDuplicateCheck/__name___matcher_equivalent_to_metric_name_overlaps - 1]
- description: __name__ matcher equivalent to metric name overlaps
  content: |
    - alert: foo
      expr: node_load1 > 5
  output: |
    1 | - alert: foo
                 ^^^
                 This rule uses a different query but it can select the same time series as the `foo` alert
                 at `fake.yml:2`, which means both rules will create identical alerts that might be
                 deduplicated, with no way to distinguish between them.
  problem:
    reporter: rule/duplicate
    summary: duplicated alerting rule
    details: ""
    diagnostics:
        - message: This rule uses a different query but it can select the same time series as the `foo` alert at `fake.yml:2`, which means both rules will create identical alerts that might be deduplicated, with no way to distinguish between them.
          firstcolumn: 1
          lastcolumn: 3
          kind: 0
    lines:
        first: 1
        last: 2
    severity: 1
    anchor: 0

